com.betfair.cougar.api.security

Interface IdentityTokenResolver<I,O,C>


  • public interface IdentityTokenResolver<I,O,C>
    Base credential resolver interface. This interface is intended to be extended per transport to provide the resolving, writing and rewriting capabilities required per transport.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • resolve

        List<IdentityToken> resolve(I input,
                          C transportAuthTokens)
        Resolve a set of identity tokens, which in turn will be used to resolve identity, from the request. Examples of a credential are a username, a password, or an SSO token.
        Parameters:
        input - the data from which the tokens will be read.
        transportAuthTokens - - the set of transport level tokens (certificates in an Http transport)
        Returns:
        a set of credentials resolved from the request

      • rewrite

        void rewrite(List<IdentityToken> credentials,
           O output)
        Allows the credentials to be re-written to the output. This may be necessary, for example, in the case of an SSO token, where a new token has been issued, and this new token must now be supplied to the client.
        Parameters:
        credentials - the credentials to rewrite
        output - the output to which the token wil be written

      • isRewriteSupported

        boolean isRewriteSupported()
        is rewriting the tokens to the output supported
